This paper discusses the use of deep neural language models for text generation, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of likelihood as a training and decoding objective, which is a common technique in machine learning and falls under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of decoding strategies, which is a common technique in neural networks and falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses the quality of machine-generated text, which can be evaluated using computer vision techniques, falling under the category of computer vision (cs.CV).
